{"title_page": "British Territorial Army Order of Battle (January 1947)", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n{{Lead rewrite|date=March 2020}}\n}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n\nFollowing the end of hostilities, by 1946 most territorial artillery regiments had been either disbanded or placed in suspended animation. On 1 January 1947 many of these battalions/regiments were reconstituted and many new regiments were formed as part of the reformed and re-organised Territorial Army (TA).  All units will be shown as they were on 1 January 1947, and not those who joined later that year, although notes on that unit's changes during that year will be shown.\n\n== Eastern Command ==\n[[Eastern Command (United Kingdom)|'''Eastern Command''']], [[Colchester]] covered the counties of: [[Essex]], [[Cambridgeshire]], [[Northamptonshire]], [[Bedfordshire]], [[Hertfordshire]], [[Norfolk]], [[Suffolk]], [[Buckinghamshire]], [[Middlesex]] (excluding [[City of London]]), [[Sussex]], [[Surrey]], [[Hampshire]], [[Kent]], and\n\n* Headquarters Eastern Command, [[Colchester]]\n* 61st Headquarters Signal Regiment, Royal Corps of Signals , [[Bedford]]\n* 2/20th (East Anglian) Army Signal Regiment, Royal Corps of Signals , [[Wanstead]]\n* 101st Tank Transporter Column, [[Royal Army Service Corps]] \n* 105th Transport Column, [[Royal Army Service Corps]] , [[Barking, London|Barking]]\n* 23rd Ordnance Field Park, [[Royal Army Ordnance Corps]] , [[Chelsea, London|Chelsea]]\n* 23rd Corps Workshop, [[Royal Electrical and Mechanical Engineers]] \n* 6th (Eastern) General Hospital, [[Royal Army Medical Corps]] \n* 24th (Eastern) Field Dressing Station, [[Royal Army Medical Corps]] \n* 163rd (East Anglian) Field Dressing Station, [[Royal Army Medical Corps]] , [[Norwich]]\n* 4th (Eastern) Casualty Clearing Station, [[Royal Army Medical Corps]] \n*[[161st Independent Infantry Brigade (United Kingdom)|'''161st Independent Infantry Brigade''']] , [[Cambridge]]\n** HQ 161